2. Optimization Strategy:
The reference examples show optimizing UTF-8 operations by adding fast paths for simple cases. We can apply a similar principle here:
- First check string lengths to quickly skip mismatches
- Add fast path for ASCII characters (common case) before full case-insensitive comparison
- Reduce iterator overhead by working directly with page data when possible

3. Selected Optimization:
The highest impact change would be to add length checking before comparison. This is:
- Simple to implement
- Doesn't change behavior
- Can eliminate many comparisons quickly
- Works well with the existing structure

4. Final Optimization Idea:
Modify `FindI` to:
- Get the search string length once at start
- Compare lengths before doing case-insensitive comparison
- Keep the same iteration structure but add the length check

